{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01Teyi6tsAsQAFMmB3VVdWVz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see it clearly. In production, the `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` uses `clusterPodPlacementConfig.Spec.NamespaceSelector` as the webhook's `NamespaceSelector`. When the CPPC has a `NamespaceSelector` matching all namespaces, the webhook fires for all namespaces. But the `shouldIgnorePod` function at line 438 checks `strings.HasPrefix(pod.Namespace, \"kube-\")`.\n\n`openshift-kube-apiserver` does NOT start with `kube-`, so it would NOT be filtered by `shouldIgnorePod`. This means a pod in `openshift-kube-apiserver` would actually GET the scheduling gate, not be excluded.\n\nUnless... the task is asking me to write a test that verifies a behavior that the code implements via some other mechanism. Let me look more carefully at the `shouldIgnorePod` or maybe there's an `openshift-` prefix check too:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1317,"cache_read_input_tokens":65423,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1317,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"08825ee3-2822-4cb7-9a97-2ce6ebb55753","uuid":"c104fb8c-ab9e-4f0c-9e55-81615d18c311","timestamp":"2026-07-20T13:33:49.078Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDPtAMXdmP2i4snKgbRm"}
